propInfo.ownerExprience: Sunrise Senior Living’s unique resident-centered services are delivered by a team trained to enable freedom of choice, encourage independence, preserve dignity, and protect the privacy of each resident. This approach enables us to continue championing quality of life for all seniors — it’s been our mission since 1981, and it’s what has made Sunrise Senior Living the premier provider of senior living services.
propInfo.staffDescription: Our Department of Health Services is headed by a Registered Nurse. Our care staff is made up of LVN's, Med Tech's and CNA's and is located in offices on each residential floor. We have a dedicated Memory Care Floor called the Terrace, where all needed levels of care are included. In assisted living we offer Medication Management, Dressing and Bathing, Escort/Transfer service and Toileting or Incontinence Care. We also have a Hospice Care Waiver.
propInfo.communityDescription: Dine in our elegant and sunny dining room or light-filled cafe, enjoy our large outdoor patio, exercise in our Fitness Center or pamper yourself in our Hair Salon. Relax or read the newspaper in our living room/library. Catch our exercise classes, lectures and discussions, concerts, outings, art classes, games, shopping trips and daily movies. Walk or use our shuttle for doctor visits; we are very close to many renowned medical offices and facilities. Life at Rhoda Goldman Plaza awaits.
propInfo.managementCompany: Scott Street Senior Housing, a Non-Profit Organization

propInfo.communityDescription:
AgeSong at Laguna Grove in San Francisco offers specialized meaning-based elder care for high needs assisted living, innovative forgetfulness care (what others call memory care, dementia care or Alzheimer's disease care), behavioral health care, coordination of scheduled nursing services, clinical care, and hospice care. Located in San Francisco's vibrant Hayes Valley neighborhood, the community at AgeSong Laguna Grove offers assisted living in a modern airy building which features abundant natural light and panoramic views from Zen and rooftop gardens, providing a therapeutic feel throughout.

The residential care programs at AgeSong at Laguna Grove offer a different approach to elder care, by integrating our inner community with our outer surroundings, and by offering residents encouragement, support, and opportunities for growth. Our high needs assisted living, and dementia care programs encourage learning and community involvement.

propInfo.communityDescription:
AgeSong WoodPark provides outstanding care to residents in the newly renovated AgeSong community. We strive to create an environment that is culturally and economically diverse. 
Our convenient location right in the heart of Oakland provides such a rich, colorful, and culturally diverse atmosphere. With an open floor plan throughout, the building is tied together by peaceful courtyards that provide healing environments for our residents.  We have common areas in every corner, such as our garden room that overlooks our green backyard, or our “AgeSong Cinema” where we view films that travel back in time or take us to the future on our modern wall projector. AgeSong WoodPark is right off the I-580 and minutes away from the Fruitvale BART Station.

propInfo.communityDescription:
AgeSong University provides outstanding care to residents in the newest AgeSong community. We strive to create an environment that is culturally and economically diverse. Since 1884 the site has continually evolved to meet the changing needs of the aging population in San Francisco, and that process continues today.

Our elegant front parlor has a fireplace, comfortable seating, and a grand piano and the circular driveway in front of the building, along with the adjacent parking, simplifies transportation issues. The spacious, cheerful dining room has floor-to-ceiling windows (pictured above) and visitors are welcome, and the bright sunroom is perfect for residents who play cards or games, or have small gatherings. There is also the chapel, with its wood-beam ceiling, is a peaceful place where non-denominational services are held on Sundays, as well as the private backyard and garden features benches, raised planters, accessible walking paths, and is safely enclosed by a fence and locking gates. AgeSong University is close to public transportation by Muni (Lines #29, #44, and #52) and BART.
